      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): prevent silent misparse of multi-colon delivery targets",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where `parseTelegramTarget` silently misparses malformed multi-colon Telegram delivery targets. A target like `chatId:topic:42:99` (4 colon-separated segments) is greedily split into `chatId: \"chatId:topic:42\"` and `messageThreadId: 99`, embedding `:topic:42` residue in the chat ID. This corrupts session keys, breaks chat type resolution, and causes downstream Telegram API calls to fail with \"chat not found\".\n\nThe same bug class affects the explicit `:topic:` parser (`a:b:topic:42` → `chatId: \"a:b\"` with `messageThreadId: 42`) and malformed t.me-looking URLs (`t.me/foo:bar:9` → `chatId: \"t.me/foo:bar\"` with `messageThreadId: 9`).\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nA shared `hasOversplitColons` guard is applied to both suffix parsers:\n1. **Topic parser** (`(.+?):topic:(\\\\d+)$`): Non-greedy preserves URL forms like `t.me/mychannel:topic:9`. The guard checks that any colon-bearing extracted chatId matches the valid t.me lookup shape from `normalizeTelegramLookupTarget`.\n2. **Colon parser** (`(.+):(\\\\d+)$`): Same guard. Greedy preserves `https://t.me/mychannel:9`. Malformed inputs with unexpected colons (including `t.me/foo:bar:9` where the extracted chatId is not a valid lookup target) fall back to full-string.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- **Valid targets**: No impact. Numeric IDs, `@username`, `chatId:topic:N`, `chatId:N`, `t.me/...:N`, `t.me/...:topic:N`, and `https://t.me/...:topic:N` all produce identical results.\n- **Malformed multi-colon targets**: Now fall through to an honest full-string fallback instead of silently producing wrong chat IDs. Prevents session key drift and \"chat not found\" delivery errors.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Terminal proof (14/14 assertions pass)\n\n```\n── Valid t.me URL-form targets preserved ──\n  ✅ 1. t.me/handle:N\n  ✅ 2. https t.me/handle:N\n  ✅ 3. t.me/handle:topic:N\n  ✅ 4. https t.me/handle:topic:N\n\n── Malformed t.me-looking targets rejected ──\n  ✅ 5. https://t.me/foo:bar:9\n  ✅ 6. t.me/foo:bar:9\n\n── Multi-colon misparse → full-string fallback ──\n  ✅ 7. chatId:topic:42:99\n  ✅ 8. a:b:topic:42\n  ✅ 9. deeply nested\n\n── Regression: valid formats unchanged ──\n  ✅ 10. plain numeric\n  ✅ 11. @username\n  ✅ 12. chatId:topic:N\n  ✅ 13. chatId:N\n  ✅ 14. prefix stripping\n\n  14 passed, 0 failed\n```\n\n### Tests and lint\n```bash\n$ pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  47 passed (47)\n\n$ npx oxlint extensions/telegram/src/targets.ts extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Exit: 0\n```\n\n### Commit history (4 substantive commits)\n1. `74884f1`: Prevent silent misparse of multi-colon delivery targets\n2. `e71f5bb`: Also guard `:topic:` parser against colon-bearing chatIds\n3. `937d099`: Use colon guard that preserves URL-form targets\n4. `a9a74dc`: Unify oversplit guard across both suffix parsers\n5. `cdd2882`: Tighten t.me guard to valid lookup target shape",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-target-multiple-colon-misparse",
